soundsync (0.0.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Installer-robustness fixes (see research/installer-readiness-2026-06-14.md):
  * G1 (critical): the appliance-user conffile variable is renamed from USER to
    SOUNDSYNC_USER. The old USER= name collided with the ambient $USER (which is
    "root" under "sudo apt install"); postinst now parses SOUNDSYNC_USER= from
    /etc/default/soundsync textually (no shell sourcing), so an untouched
    conffile yields an empty SS_USER and the sole-human auto-detect runs instead
    of pinning linger to root and killing the headless daemon at boot.
  * G6: postinst purge now removes the WirePlumber config paths the binary
    actually writes (wireplumber.conf.d/51-soundsync*.conf and
    bluetooth.lua.d/51-soundsync*) instead of a bogus .lua.d directory, so the
    0.4.x Lua config is no longer orphaned on purge.
  * G12: prerm now acts only on remove|deconfigure, not on upgrade. Upgrades no
    longer stop the Class-of-Device watcher mid-upgrade or double-manage the
    user unit; postinst reconciles unit state.
  * G11: add pipewire-bin (pw-cat/pw-cli/pw-link/pw-metadata/pw-loopback) and
    curl to Depends; previously present only transitively.
  * N13: replace the 'systemctl is-system-running --quiet' guard (which
    false-negatives on a degraded system) with the dh-standard
    '[ -d /run/systemd/system ]' chroot guard when starting the system units.

 -- SoundSync Maintainers <soundsync@example.com>  Sun, 14 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0000

soundsync (0.0.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Ship + enable the Class-of-Device watcher unit in the .deb so the adapter
    stays advertised as an audio speaker, matching install.sh (NF-9).
  * postinst now enables systemd linger for the appliance user so the headless
    user daemon starts at boot without an interactive login (NF-10). The user
    is taken from USER= in /etc/default/soundsync, else auto-detected as the
    sole human login account; otherwise a remediation note is printed.
  * postinst restarts the appliance user's WirePlumber after writing the A2DP
    config, but only when that user's session bus is live (NF-31). Without a
    live session the config loads at the next boot/login.
  * Ship a commented /etc/default/soundsync (conffile) to select the appliance
    user for linger + WirePlumber restart.

 -- SoundSync Maintainers <soundsync@example.com>  Sat, 14 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

soundsync (0.0.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial packaging: Bluetooth A2DP sink daemon with DSP EQ + web UI.
  * Installs systemd user service (soundsync.service) and root oneshot
    adapter-setup service (soundsync-adapter.service).
  * Applies WirePlumber A2DP config at install time via
    soundsync apply-wireplumber-config.

 -- SoundSync Maintainers <soundsync@example.com>  Sat, 07 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
